                <fr:title text="a bijective enumeration of the integers">a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KR.xml" title="bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">bijective</fr:link> enumeration of the integers</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>We can define a bijective enumeration of the integers by “zigzagging” between the positive and the negative following the pattern<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (0, -1, 1,-2,2,-3,3,\ldots \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>:</html:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
  e&\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  \mathbb {Z}\\
  e{\mathopen {}\left (i\right )\mathclose {}} &=
  \begin {cases}
   0 &\text {when } i=0\\
   i\div  2 &\text {when } i > 0 \land  2\mid  i\\
   -{\mathopen {}\left (i+1\right )\mathclose {}}\div  2 &\text {when } i > 0 \land  \lnot {\mathopen {}\left (2\mid  i\right )\mathclose {}}
  \end {cases}
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
              </fr:mainmatter>
