                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>The cartesian product of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MH.xml" title="countable set" addr="jms-00MH" type="local">countable</fr:link> sets is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MH.xml" title="countable set" addr="jms-00MH" type="local">countable</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-00ML/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00ML/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="cartesian product of countable sets › forest://jonmsterling/jms-00ML/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00ML.xml" title="cartesian product of countable sets" addr="jms-00ML" type="local">cartesian product of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MH.xml" title="countable set" addr="jms-00MH" type="local">countable sets</fr:link></fr:link> › jms-00ML/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MH.xml" title="countable set" addr="jms-00MH" type="local">countable</fr:link> sets. If either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is empty, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex> is empty and thus <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MH.xml" title="countable set" addr="jms-00MH" type="local">countable</fr:link>. Otherwise, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_A\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_B\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00ME.xml" title="enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerations</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> respectively. Then the function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_A\times  e_B\colon  \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}\to  A\times  B]]></fr:tex> can be seen to be <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>; letting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> be any enumeration of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>, can compose to obtain a surjection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (e_A\times  e_B\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  f\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A\times  B]]></fr:tex> by <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MD.xml" title="closure of surjections under identity and composition" addr="jms-00MD" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00MD" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
