            <fr:title text="non-empty subsets of enumerable sets are enumerable › forest://jonmsterling/jms-00MK/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MK.xml" title="non-empty subsets of enumerable sets are enumerable" addr="jms-00MK" type="local">non-empty subsets of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00ME.xml" title="enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link> sets are <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00ME.xml" title="enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link></fr:link> › jms-00MK/0</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We will use the same method as in our proof of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MI.xml" title="alternative definition of countability" addr="jms-00MI" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00MI" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> be a non-empty subset of an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00ME.xml" title="enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link> set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, so that we have some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex>. We define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e'\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow {S}]]></fr:tex> to send <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (i\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (i\right )\mathclose {}}\in  S]]></fr:tex> and to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> otherwise.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
